'''The Center for Research in Agricultural Genomics''' (CRAG)<ref name="Centre de Recerca en Agrigenomica">{{cite web|title=Centre de Recerca en Agrigenomica|url=http://www.cragenomica.es}}</ref>  is located at the Campus UAB in [[Bellaterra]]. As a public consortium incorporating research groups from the [[Consejo Superior de Investigaciones Cientificas]] and the [[Universitat Autonoma de Barcelona]] (UAB) and [[Catalan Institution for Research and Advanced Studies|ICREA]] researchers, it is devoted to the study of the genomics and genetics of agriculturally important plants and farm animals.

